<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1146,1452]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<materialsCitation box="[198,965,1186,1212]" collectionCode="ZMB" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" specimenCode="ZMB 2635" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="syntype">
<typeStatus box="[198,294,1186,1212]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Syntype</typeStatus>
(marked with type * in Peters´ handwriting): 
<specimenCode box="[833,965,1186,1212]" collectionCode="ZMB" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="Museum">ZMB 2635</specimenCode>
</materialsCitation>
, 
<materialsCitation collectionCode="RMNH" collectorName="Id. &amp; Reinwardt" country="Moluccas, Indonesia" location="Moluccas, Indonesia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="syntype">
skin and skull, male, adult; Ternate 
<collectorName box="[1396,1430,1186,1212]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Id.</collectorName>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,396,1226,1252]" isEnumeration="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Moluccas, Indonesia</collectingCountry>
; collected by 
<collectorName box="[558,683,1226,1252]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Reinwardt</collectorName>
, 1821, in exchange from 
<collectionCode box="[980,1072,1226,1252]" country="Netherlands" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34992" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34992" name="National Museum of Natural History, Naturalis" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="Museum">RMNH</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1146,1452]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="RMNH" collectorName="Jentink &amp; Reinwardt" country="Indonesia" location="Ternate" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" specimenCode="ZMB 2635" specimenCount="4" typeStatus="syntype">
Comment: Temminck described this species on the basis of 
<specimenCount box="[913,1088,1266,1292]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
[
<typeStatus box="[1104,1216,1266,1292]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">syntypes</typeStatus>
]. These 
<specimenCount pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
had been preserved in the 
<collectionCode box="[530,618,1306,1332]" country="Netherlands" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34992" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34992" name="National Museum of Natural History, Naturalis" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="Museum">RMNH</collectionCode>
collections alledgedly until 1888 (
<collectorName box="[1027,1118,1306,1332]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Jentink</collectorName>
: 140), but 
<bibRefCitation author="Matschie, P." pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refId="ref46535" refString="Matschie, P. (1899) Die Fledermause des Berliner Museums fur Naturkunde, 1. Megachiroptera. Berlin, 1 - 107, G. Reimer Verlag" type="book" year="1899">Matschie (1899: 32)</bibRefCitation>
reported only 
<specimenCount box="[367,528,1346,1372]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[604,691,1346,1372]" name="Indonesia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Ternate</collectingCountry>
(leg. 
<collectorName box="[762,886,1346,1372]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Reinwardt</collectorName>
) was present in 
<collectionCode box="[1083,1175,1346,1372]" country="Netherlands" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34992" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34992" name="National Museum of Natural History, Naturalis" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="Museum">RMNH</collectionCode>
. 
<specimenCode box="[1188,1319,1346,1372]" collectionCode="ZMB" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="Museum">ZMB 2635</specimenCode>
is a catalogue number given by Peters presumably in the 1860s. So Peters had received this specimen long before he died (1883). 
<specimenCode box="[301,430,1426,1452]" collectionCode="ZMB" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="Museum">ZMB 2635</specimenCode>
is supposed to be one of the 
<specimenCount box="[771,944,1426,1452]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
used by Temminck for the description
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
